# Lesson 2
# Pseudo-code

1) method that returns the sum of two integers

get first number
get second number
make sure they're integers
add them together
print the result

START
GET num_1
GET num_2
SET result = num1.to_i + num2.to_i
PRINT result
END


2) Method that takes an array of strings, then returns a string that is
all those strings concatenated together

set a base, empty string
read each element in the array and add it to the base string
display the base string

START
SET string = ""
SET iterator = 0
WHILE iterator < length of array
  SET temp = array(iterator)
  string = string + temp
  iterator = iterator + 1
PRINT string
END


3) method that takes an array of integers, and returns a new array with every other element

read each element of an array
if its index is odd, add it to a new array
display the new array

START
SET final_array = []
SET iterator = 0
WHILE iterator < length of base_array
  IF iterator.odd?
    SET final_array << base_array(iterator)
  ELSE don't
iterator = iterator + 1
PRINT final_array
END
